It was just another quiet evening at the Golden Harbor Hotel. The grand lobby gleamed under soft chandeliers, its ornate marble floors echoing the sound of your shoes as you made your rounds. As a concierge, you’d grown used to the routine: helping guests, answering calls, tidying up. But tonight, something felt different.
While clearing the front desk, you noticed something tucked beneath the edge of a chair, shimmering faintly under the lights, almost as if it produced light on its own. Curious, you bent down and picked it up. The intricate design stole your breath away, and before you could fully take it all in, a frail voice interrupted your focus. “Excuse me, young one.” You turned to see an elderly woman, small and hunched with age, her wrinkled hands clutching the edge of the counter. Her eyes were wide with worry, glistening with tears that hadn’t yet fallen.
“I...I believe you found something of mine,” she whispered, her voice trembling. “A coin...a very special coin. I lost it, and...it means the world to me.”
The coin in your pocket suddenly felt heavier. There was no way she could have seen you pick it up, but as you looked into her tear-filled eyes, you knew there was more to this than coincidence.
You could sense an almost magnetic attraction between the coin and...and...the woman. Not you. That made you feel sad. It was being drawn back to its earner. Wait, not earner—owner. It was being drawn back to its owner. But you get the distinct feeling that this coin was the result of accomplishment, not happy chance. It was too beautiful. Gold coins usually don’t have other colors on them. You wish you could look at it again, but sensing the woman’s anguish, you quickly grasp the coin in your pocket.

She smiles faintly, turns around without a word, and walks off.
Now you feel empty inside. You know you will never see such a coin ever again in your lifetime, but how would coin collecting be for a hobby? You don’t have any hobbies, and apparently coins can have real power. As you look around the lobby, you start to wonder where more coins might be hiding. Maybe there is someone who could help you get started, but for now, just start looking.

The Coinmaster
◀
Lvl 2
▶
"Greetings, friend. My name is Mardin Goldwhisper, and I...am the Coinmaster. I've always been drawn to the stories that every coin carries, each one a small piece of history passed down through countless hands. As you step into my cluttered little shop, you'll find me nestled among shelves of tarnished copper, shining silver, and glimmering gold, each coin telling a tale of its own. I'm not just a collector; I'm a keeper of memories, a guardian of forgotten times. I’ve spent a lifetime studying these relics, learning their secrets, and now, I see potential in you. If you’re willing, I’d be more than happy to share what I know, to teach you the delicate art of recognizing value where others might see only metal."
"Ah, you've discovered the Seekers! These aren't your ordinary helpers, mind you—they're not entirely human, more like ancient constructs built for one purpose: to find coins. Once set loose, they'll scour the land for you, tirelessly searching while you focus on bigger things. But there's a catch—they run on fuel. Keep them powered, and they'll do wonders for your coin collecting, but forget to fuel them, and they'll grind to a halt. They might also just up and decide to quit, through no fault of your own. However, they rally behind their strongest, even the memory of their strongest. Tend to them well, and they'll make you rich faster than your hands ever could."
"I'd say you're getting the hang of this. Your powers are growing, but you still have much to learn. With every coin you find, you must be getting curious about how much harder it will be to find the rest of the coins. In the Statistics tab, you will find a plethora of new statistics at your disposal to satisfy your growing curiosity. After all, the scope of your search is about to grow vastly."
"When you were a child, I bet you used to check the vending machine coin returns to see if you could find a few coins that people forgot to collect after buying something. There is a vending machine I bet you didn't know about. It's right around the corner here. You should check it every now and then."
"You have discovered the final type of coin, but you still have a long, long way to go to complete your collection. With every coin you find, it gets harder to find the next one. Don't worry, young one, there are more places to look. In time, you will find them."
"Your Seekers look well tended. Well done! They will hunt relentlessly for you. All they need is fuel. But do you know what drives them absolutely nuts? Super Seeker Pills, filled with equal parts cabbage and peppermint, of all things. For whatever reason, it makes them even more relentless in their search, for about 30 seconds at least. Here are 10 pills. Use them wisely. You might be able to find more later if you are resourceful and know the right people."
"Ever wonder why people throw coins into fountains? Most folks think it's all about wishes, but that's only part of the story. It dates back to ancient times, when people believed water spirits controlled the flow of life itself. Offering a coin was a way to show respect—or bribe, if you will—the spirits for blessings, like good health or safe travels. How foolish. Lay out a clear net in the fountain so no one will see, and go back to collect the coins later when nobody is around. Hey, maybe you are actually the water spirit.
"Felix the Traveling Salesman is a legend among collectors. He doesn't just deal in coins; he unearths treasures with stories etched into their surfaces. He's got a knack for finding the rare ones—the coins minted in forgotten kingdoms or those marked with minting errors so unique they're one-of-a-kind. He's not cheap, mind you, and he's as slippery as quicksilver. But if there's a coin you need, Felix is your man. Just be ready to barter, for he doesn't stay in one place for long."
"Ah, metal detecting on the beach—now there's a pastime that stirs the heart. It's not just about finding treasure; it's about the thrill of discovery, the whisper of history beneath your feet. Beaches, you see, are natural collectors of stories—coins dropped from pockets, rings lost in hurried swims, even relics washed ashore from shipwrecks long forgotten. With the steady hum of your detector and the anticipation in your chest, every beep is a question: what lies beneath? That's the magic of it—every sweep of the sand holds a world of possibilities."
"Buying coin rolls from the bank—now there's a clever game for the patient collector. It's like panning for gold in a stream of modern currency. Most people think those rolls are just pocket change, but they're treasure troves for the discerning eye. Every so often, you'll find a wheat penny, a silver dime, or even a rare error coin that slipped through the mint's watchful gaze. It's all about persistence and knowing what to look for—those tiny details that turn a nickel into a small fortune. Best part? You're not losing a thing; whatever you don't keep, you can spend. It's the thrill of the hunt, wrapped up in everyday commerce."
"Your powers are getting strong indeed. We veteran coin collectors find so many coins so quickly that we grow weary of making note of the common ones we find that we already have. You will now no longer get notifications about common coins you already have, but you can turn them back on in Settings if you'd like. Keep searching!"
"Imagine this—a robotic coin vacuum, gliding across the parking lot with quiet precision. Equipped with advanced sensors and a sharp eye for glints of metal, it sweeps through cracks and crevices where loose change loves to hide. This little marvel doesn't just suck up coins; it catalogs them in real-time, identifying dates, mint marks, and even potential errors before depositing them neatly into a collection tray. It's the ultimate tool for the modern treasure hunter—turning the mundane sprawl of a parking lot into a field of endless possibility. No more sore backs or scuffed knees—just effortless discovery."
"The bankers don't like to sell too many coin rolls to the same person. But you've been a patron for a while now, and from the sound of it, they are beginning to trust you more and more. They are now willing to sell you more coin rolls and more frequently. Keep it up, and your renown will earn you even more trust."
"Ah, the allure of the coin pusher. Those gleaming towers of coins, teetering on the edge, are more than just a test of luck—they're a treasure hunter's secret playground. Hidden among the avalanche of ordinary coins, you might spot a rare state quarter, an older silver coin, or even a misprint. It's all about timing and strategy—nudging the right coin at the right moment to send the riches cascading. Sure, it's a gamble, but every push carries the promise of a jackpot far greater than the flashing lights and jingling chimes—a piece of history waiting to be claimed. Load it up with coins and watch it work."
"You've scoured coin rolls, swept the parking lots, searched the vending machines, dragged the fountain, raked the beach, bartered with the traveling salesman, and risked it all with the coin pusher. The easy finds are all gone, but the real treasures are still out there. You're in the home stretch, but if you ever want to find them all, you are going to have to focus and really ramp up your powers. You won't see me again until it's done. Good luck!"
"You've done well! Each coin tells a story, indeed, does it not? There are many Coinmasters out there. I am not sure how you came to know me as 'the' Coinmaster. You will soon meet The Collector—the Supreme Being who trained me and countless others. I am but a pupil myself. While each Coinmaster trains many young collectors, The Collector trains Coinmasters. Listen to what 'It' has to say, and your collection will continue to flourish. Your training with me is now complete. Maybe one day you'll be able to teach me a thing or two. Farewell."
"Yes. Unlock one..."
"Maybe there is hope for you yet. Most who complete a collection never care to complete a second. Just how many do you have the strength to complete?"
"You have ascended several times, but you have far yet to go. You trained under that fool Mardin, yes? You will surpass him quickly, no doubt. He is old and losing his ambition. But you seem different... The stretch from now is long and arduous, and most lose their way. Will you?"
"We have not spoken for a while.You are halfway there, but truth be told, the last half takes no time at all. I will be waiting for you near the end."
"Your powers are strong, and your drive is impeccable. You passed that fool Mardin a while back, and I think he has since walked away from collecting altogether. But you... You are about to see what it is to be a Grandmaster. By now you have completed at least one specialization and received the reward coin. These coins are more than just physical coins. They themselves are alive and embody the virtues one must have to be a true collector. When all nine are together in proximity, their true power is revealed."
"You have just earned the last of The Nine. You are only the second to do so and become a Grandmaster. My last one was the Clicking coin. I thought it looked very dull compared with the rest. But then I saw them all begin to glow when I put them together. What happened next, there are no words to describe. When you are ready, you must..."

Every time you buy the Lvl 100 upgrade, you "ascend". Every time you "descend", you return to Lvl 1 to complete another collection. You may choose a specialization but must first unlock it by completing another descension. Each specialization requires 10 descensions to fully complete, but the rewards are enormous.

From now on, here are the perks:
  • All coins will be available to find at Lvl 1.
  • All specials will be unlocked at Lvl 1 with powers extrapolated exponentially.
  • Every ascension will strengthen all powers by 10%.
You have obtained the final specialization coin. You should visit The Collector for further instruction.

Master of Ascending
Coin of the Grandmaster
Congratulations, Grandmaster! As you place the last of nine specialization coins into position, a brilliant light radiates from them. Each coin, once ordinary and powerless on its own, now glows with an otherworldly energy. Together, they form "The Nine"—a united force of unimaginable strength and harmony. The air crackles with potential as their combined power is summoned, revealing secrets and wonders hidden for centuries. The powers from the nine coins are trying to coalesce...

You’ve done it—by bringing these coins together, you’ve unlocked the true power of The Nine,
proving that unity is greater than the sum of its parts.
Wait, this coin looks familiar. You have seen it before. But where?

Yes, you do remember now. The elderly woman who lost her coin in your hotel all those years ago (hover over the picture). That shimmering coin. You almost kept it. You are very glad you didn't. You now appreciate the hard work that went into obtaining a coin like that. Working hard pays off. Now get back out into the world, work hard, and do some good. In the meantime, there are always coins out there to find. There may be some achievements you still want to go for. You may return and continue collecting now, or you may also perform a Hard Reset in Settings to start the journey over again.
